# Type (required): Describes the purpose of the commit
#   feat:     A new feature
#   fix:      A bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation only changes
#   style:    Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code
#   refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   test:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
#   chore:    Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools
#   perf:     A code change that improves performance
#   ci:       Changes to CI configuration files and scripts
#   revert:   Reverts a previous commit
#
# Scope (optional): The scope of the commit (e.g., component, module, file)
# Subject (required): Brief description using imperative mood
# Body (optional): Detailed description of the changes
# Footer (optional): References to issues, breaking changes, etc.
# ======================================================================

# Type (required): feat|fix|docs|style|refactor|test|chore|perf|ci|revert
# Scope (optional): module, component, file, etc.
# Subject (required): brief description in imperative mood, no more than 80 characters
# Example: feat(Utility): add user authentication service

# Body (optional): detailed description of changes and reasoning
# Wrap at 72 characters. Use | for line breaks if needed.
What:


How/Why:

# Footer (optional): references to issues, breaking changes, etc.
# Example: Closes #123, BREAKING CHANGE: API interface modified
# Footer: 

